[5] Hong Kong - Ex Malaysia
Date: 09 Jan 2007
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: News.gov.hk - Hong Kong, 9 Jan 2006 [edited]
<http://www.news.gov.hk/en/category/healthandcommunity/070109/html/070109en05008.htm>

The Centre for Health Protection has confirmed the 1st imported
Dengue fever case of 2007, involving a 31-year-old Tuen Mun woman.
She travelled to Malaysia 24-31 Dec [2006] and came down with fever,
headache, a rash, and muscle and joint pain on 2 Jan [2007]. She was
admitted to Tuen Mun Hospital on 6 Jan [2007] and is now in stable condition.
Her travel companions have no symptoms.
